<recipe>
    <name>Pork Roast With Root Vegetables</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Meat should be tied with string in order to keep its shape during cooking and to be roasted evenly.

2. Mix the chopped rosemary, sage, minced garlic, salt and pepper. Rub the meat all over with spice mixture. 

3. Heat half the oil over medium heat in a pan (cast iron is preferable) and add the meat.

4. Sear it on all sides, 8 to 10 minutes, then place it into the oven (if you do not have a pan suitable for both stovetop and oven, use large frying pan and later transfer the meat into a baking tray).

5. Mix the rest of the oil, Dijon mustard, thyme and garlic powder in a small bowl. 

6. Put the vegetables in a large bowl, pour the mustard mixture over and season generously with salt and pepper. Toss well to coat all the vegetables. 

7. After 15 minutes add the vegetables into a baking pan and place them in the oven.

8. Pork should be roasted until the thermometer inserted in the center of meat registers 140 degrees F (about 1 hour). 

9. Transfer pork to a cutting board, cover with aluminum foil and let it rest for 15 minutes before slicing. 

10. Serve warm with roasted vegetables, a side salad and sauerkraut.

* Make enough pork roast to have for tomorrow's lunch.</instructions>
